@startuml fig-A10-message-flow
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Network Hardening — E2 PCAP Flow (Allowed vs Blocked Connections)

participant "frontend\n:8080" as FE #FFE0B2
participant "DOCKER-USER\n(iptables)" as DU #FCE4EC
participant "backend\n:5000" as BE #BBDEFB
participant "db\n:3306" as DB #E1BEE7
participant "h2\n(external)" as EXT #FFCDD2
participant "tcpdump\n(bridge)" as CAP #ECEFF1

== ALLOWED: frontend → backend ==

FE -[#43A047]> DU : SYN → backend:5000
DU -[#43A047]> BE : allowed by rule
BE -[#43A047]-> DU : SYN-ACK
DU -[#43A047]-> FE : SYN-ACK
FE -[#43A047]> BE : ACK + HTTP request
BE -[#43A047]-> FE : HTTP 200
note right of CAP : R1: tcp || udp >= 10\ncomplete handshake visible

== ALLOWED: backend → db ==

BE -[#43A047]> DU : SYN → db:3306
DU -[#43A047]> DB : allowed by rule
DB -[#43A047]-> BE : SYN-ACK
BE -[#43A047]> DB : ACK + query

== BLOCKED: frontend → db (segmentation) ==

FE -[#E53935]> DU : SYN → db:3306
DU -[#E53935]>x DU : DROP (DOCKER-USER rule)
note right of DU #FFCDD2 : SYN without reply in PCAP\n(no SYN-ACK, no RST)

== BLOCKED: container → external (egress) ==

FE -[#E53935]> DU : SYN → h2:80
DU -[#E53935]>x DU : DROP (egress filter)
note right of DU #FFCDD2 : R3: tcp.port==80 >= 1\negress attempt visible, no reply

== BLOCKED: external → db (inbound) ==

EXT -[#E53935]> DU : SYN → db:3306
DU -[#E53935]>x DU : DROP
note right of DU #FFCDD2 : direct external access denied

== DNS RESOLUTION ==

FE -> DU : DNS query (UDP/53)
note right of CAP : R2: dns || udp.port==53 >= 1

legend right
  PCAP on Docker bridge shows: complete
  handshake for allowed flows and SYN
  without progress for blocked flows.
  iptables counters confirm rule hits.
endlegend
@enduml
